(43, 12, 32, 43, 8, 28, 28, 'lifted up', 'Connection of Being Lifted Up', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of being ''lifted up.'' In John 12:32, Jesus states that he will draw all men when he is lifted up, while in John 8:28, he indicates that knowing him comes after he is lifted up. This connection highlights the significance of his crucifixion and revelation.', 'theme', 0.489, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
